title: Google\Cloud\Iap\V1\GcipSettings
name: GcipSettings
description:
Allows customers to configure tenant_id for GCIP instance per-app.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.iap.v1.GcipSettings

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.tenant_ids
params.description: GCIP tenant ids that are linked to the IAP resource. tenantids could be a string beginning with a number character to indicate authenticating with GCIP tenant flow, or in the format of to indicate authenticating with GCIP agent flow. If agent flow is used, tenant_ids should only contain one single element, while for tenant flow, tenant_ids can contain multiple elements.

params.name: data.login_page_uri
params.description: Login page URI associated with the GCIP tenants. Typically, all resources within the same project share the same login page, though it could be overridden at the sub resource level.
